        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(gitlab): add GitLab provider support",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds bounded GitLab.com and self-managed GitLab support alongside GitHub. The maintainer repair preserves the contributor's commits while tightening provider isolation, credential handling, supported surfaces, and regression coverage.\n\n## Supported GitLab surface\n\n- Account-scoped PAT authentication using the `read_api` scope and the `PRIVATE-TOKEN` header.\n- Projects, issues, merge requests, pipelines, releases, tags, branches, commits, and contributors.\n- Provider-correct app menus, web URLs, repository refresh, pinned repositories, recent lists, and CLI repository commands.\n- GitLab subgroup repository identities and local checkout matching for HTTPS and SCP-style remotes.\n- GitHub-only surfaces remain hidden or explicitly unavailable for GitLab accounts.\n\n## Security and privacy boundary\n\n- GitLab hosts must use HTTPS and cannot include URL credentials.\n- Token-bearing requests block redirects and reject responses from another origin.\n- GitLab PATs stay in account-scoped Keychain storage and cannot fall back to GitHub OAuth or legacy GitHub PAT storage.\n- No App Transport Security exception is added.\n- CLI login accepts PAT input through standard input rather than an argument.\n\n## Proof\n\n- `pnpm -s check`: SwiftFormat, SwiftLint, 679 tests in 111 suites.\n- Focused GitLab client tests cover host validation, header routing, cross-origin rejection, disabled optional features, repository counts, pipelines, and releases.\n- Local project tests cover full GitLab subgroup paths for HTTPS and SCP-style remotes.\n- Structured Codex autoreview is clean on the complete branch diff.\n- Built app and CLI have live GitHub proof.\n\nThe mandatory live GitLab app and CLI proof is still pending access to an approved safe GitLab account. Do not merge until that gate is complete and the maintainer confirms GitLab is inside RepoBar's supported product scope.\n",
        "branch": "main",
